    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Well shut in to stop produced water issues",
      "Production operators took samples of produced water outfall at six-hour intervals for four days",
      "Lab analysis conducted on samples to estimate hydrocarbon release",
      "BP developing plan to reduce liquid rate during well ramp up"
    ],
    "summary": "A pollution event occurred on 7 June 2021 at Thunder Horse platform (MC 778 A) when attempting to bring the S5 well online from a long-term shut-in. During well unloading operations using dual Float Cell (FC) operations, the liquid rate exceeded the capacity of FC 1 and FC 2, resulting in produced water issues. An estimated 4 barrels of hydrocarbons were released into the Gulf of Mexico through the produced water outfall from 7 June to 10 June 2021.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Reduce liquid rate at the beginning of ramp up to a slower pace to improve well unloading and maintain manageable Float Cell capacity"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "well unloading",
      "Float Cell operations",
      "produced water outfall",
      "long term shut-in",
      "equipment capacity exceeded",
      "hydrocarbon sheen"
    ]
  },
